videos.headline: Memphis strikes quickly with 67-yard TD
videos.description: Memphis wastes little time, needing only two plays to light up the scoreboard when Phil Mayhue is left wide open to go 67 yards to the house for a Tigers' touchdown.

videos.headline: Memphis extends lead on 1-yard TD run
videos.description: Doroland Dorceus run for 1-yard for a TD

videos.headline: Houston strikes back with Catalon TD
videos.description: Duke Catalon takes the handoff up the middle and finds the end zone from 10 yards out to score Houston's first touchdown and cut Memphis' lead to 14-10.

videos.headline: Memphis can't stop scoring with third TD of the quarter
videos.description: Memphis makes it three touchdowns on three possessions when Riley Ferguson hits Phil Mayhue from two yards out to put the Tigers ahead 21-10 in the first quarter.

videos.headline: Ward, Houston answer with 29-yard TD
videos.description: Having to keep pace with Memphis' high-flying offense, Houston answers when Greg Ward Jr. hits Tyler McCloskey over the middle for a 29-yard touchdown strike to bring the Cougars to within 21-17.

videos.headline: Memphis comes up with big interception
videos.description: Greg Ward Jr. pass intercepted Shaun Rupert return for 12-yards to the Memph 42

videos.headline: Houston's Howard Wilson ejected for targeting
videos.description: HOUSTON Penalty, Personal Foul (Howard Wilson) to the Houst 4 for a 1ST down. Howard Wilson ejected for targeting.

videos.headline: Memphis punches it in again with Henderson TD
videos.description: Darrell Henderson refuses to come up short and stays up just long enough to reach the end zone from two yards out and puts Memphis up 34-17 late in the first half.

videos.headline: Ward hits Allen for Houston 35-yard TD strike
videos.description: Houston gets a jump start to the second half when Greg Ward Jr. finds Chance Allen for the 35-yard touchdown to get the Cougars within 34-24.

videos.headline: Houston gambles on fake punt in own end and converts for a first down
videos.description: Dane Roy run for 11-yards to the Houst 48 for a 1ST down

videos.headline: Houston field goal cuts Memphis lead to one score
videos.description: Houston field goal cuts Memphis lead to one score

videos.headline: Houston cuts Memphis lead to 4 with 26-yard FG
Houston takes first lead with 55-yard TD
videos.description: After trailing for nearly the entire game, Houston finally puts itself ahead on 4th-and-1 when Linell Bonner makes the catch and is gone for a 55-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Memphis answers with Miller's 35-yard TD catch
videos.description: After Houston took the lead for the first time in the game, Memphis answers right back with a 35-yard touchdown to Anthony Miller.

videos.headline: Chance Allen gets his feet down in bounds to give Houston late lead
videos.description: Greg Ward Jr. pass complete to Chance Allen for 3-yards for a TD

videos.headline: Memphis retakes the lead with late Miller TD
videos.description: Riley Ferguson hits Anthony Miller over the middle for the 10-yard touchdown to give Memphis the lead with 19 seconds left.

videos.headline: No last second magic for Houston as Memphis gets the upset victory
videos.description: No last second magic for Houston as Memphis gets the upset victory

videos.headline: Memphis upsets Houston in thriller
videos.description: Memphis' Anthony Miller scores the go-ahead touchdown with under 30 seconds remaining in the fourth quarter as the Tigers upset No. 20 Houston 48-44.
